<br>
The guest came and then it all became clear as the confusion was solved as to the identity of the messenger. Poseidon realized he should take his leave and looked on his brother and his wife for a second longer before he walked away.<br>
<br>
The darkness of the underworld devoured the space in which Poseidon stood while he disappeared, his keen eyes are on Hecate and he waved good bye to her and was gone! <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/26/02 5:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Happy...</span><hr size=1> ::Hades simply held Persephone for a while.  He held her closely before looking into her eyes::<br>
<br>
