<br>
::With that he tenderly kissed her lips.  He noted his brother's leaving.  He would probably make an appearance in his palace later, mayhaps when Persephone slept:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/27/02 1:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aishwarya-rai.com/tradi/tash16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Privacy</span><hr size=1> ::Listening to his words Persephone kisses him back and snuggles deeply into his arms:: I do not care what my mother thinks. Most her time isn't spent time with me. She still treats me like a child and s tries teach me how to grow things, which is something I've learned already. ::Her eyes become icy in frusteraton:: And to top it of, she still calls me Kore!<br>
<br>
::After that, Persephone had an agry flashback of when she first married Hades. She remebered that he had given her the name Persephone upon her coronation because he hated the name as much as she had. She then put a soft hand upon his chest and looked up at him with her infamous light-electric blue eyes:: May we be go someplace where we can talk alone? <p>*~* Persephone...Queen of the Underworld.. faithful wife to Hades... princesss goddess of the Spring*~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/27/02 1:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Let us walk...</span><hr size=1> ::Hades smiled at her apparent frustration.  In some respects he found it amusing.  This conflict between mother and daughter, the mother's inability to let go::<br>
